quran[59]{c,v,t}:
  26,52,"Then We revealed unto Moses, “Set forth with My servants by night; you shall indeed be pursued.”"
  26,53,"Then Pharaoh sent marshalers to the cities [saying]"
  26,54,“These indeed are a small band
  26,55,and indeed they have enraged us
  26,56,and we are a host at the ready!”
  26,57,So We expelled them from gardens and springs
  26,58,and treasures and a noble station
  26,59,"So it was, and We made the Children of Israel to inherit them"
  26,60,Then they pursued them at sunrise
  26,61,"And when the two hosts saw one another, the companions of Moses said, “We are overtaken!”"
  26,62,"He said, “Nay! Truly my Lord is with me; He will guide me.”"
  26,63,"Then We revealed unto Moses, “Strike the sea with thy staff!” and it parted, and each part was as a great mountain"
  26,64,And thither We brought the others nigh
  26,65,And We delivered Moses and those with him all together
  26,66,Then We drowned the others
  26,67,"Truly in that is a sign, though most of them are not believers"
  26,68,"And truly thy Lord is the Mighty, the Merciful"
  26,69,And recite unto them the story of Abraham
  26,70,"when he said to his father and his people, “What are you worshipping?”"
  26,71,"They said, “We worship idols, and we remain ever devoted to them.”"
  26,72,"He said, “Do they hear you when you call"
  26,73,Or do they benefit or harm you?”
  26,74,"They said, “Nay, but we found our fathers doing so.”"
  26,75,"He said, “Have you considered what you worship"
  26,76,you and your ancestors
  26,77,"For they are all enemies unto me, save the Lord of the worlds"
  26,78,"Who created me, and guides me"
  26,79,and Who feeds me and gives me drink
  26,80,"and Who, when I am ill, heals me"
  26,81,"and Who causes me to die, then gives me life"
  26,82,and Who I hope will forgive me my sins on the Day of Judgment
  26,83,"My Lord! Grant me judgment, and bind me to the righteous"
  26,84,And make for me faithful renown among later generations
  26,85,And place me among the heirs of the Garden of bliss
  26,86,And forgive my father—he is one of those who are astray
  26,87,And disgrace me not on the Day they are resurrected
  26,88,the Day when neither wealth nor children avail
  26,89,save for him who comes to God with a sound heart.”
  26,90,And the Garden will be brought nigh unto the reverent
  26,91,and Hellfire will become apparent to the errant
  26,92,"And it will be said unto them, “Where is that which you worshipped"
  26,93,apart from God? Are they helping you or helping themselves?”
  26,94,"Then they shall be toppled into it, they and the errant"
  26,95,and the hosts of Iblis all together
  26,96,"They will say, as they dispute with one another therein"
  26,97,"“By God, indeed we were in manifest error"
  26,98,when we made you equal with the Lord of the worlds
  26,99,And none caused us to go astray but the guilty
  26,100,So now we have no intercessors
  26,101,nor any loyal friend
  26,102,"If we had another turn, we would be among the believers.”"
  26,103,"Truly in that is a sign, but most of them are not believers"
  26,104,"And truly thy Lord is indeed the Mighty, the Merciful"
  26,105,The people of Noah denied the messengers
  26,106,"when their brother Noah said unto them, “Will you not be reverent"
  26,107,Truly I am a trustworthy messenger unto you
  26,108,So reverence God and obey me
  26,109,And I ask not of you any reward for it; my reward lies only with the Lord of the worlds
  26,110,So reverence God and obey me.”